results.wikipedia_summary: Spinus is a genus which contains the primarily North and South American siskins and goldfinches. The taxonomy still needs to be finalized, as some taxonomists continue to use Carduelis for the genus. The SACC uses the genus Sporagra for the siskins in South America. The Eurasian siskin is the only species from the Old World included in the group.
